owl:Ontology.dc:title: Digital Construction Entities
owl:Ontology.terms:creator: Seppo Törmä
Yuan Zheng
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: Digital Construction Entities Ontology defines the essential entities that can be referred to in construction and renovation projects by people or systems.
owl:Ontology.rdfs:label: Digital Construction Entities

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Def: A process that is intentionally performed by an agent.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Activity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The actors and stakeholders of construction projects.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Constituent of a construction entity with a characteristic technical function, form or position.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: BuildingObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Minimum bounding box of an entity given by a minimum cartesian position and maximum cartesian position
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CartesianBoundingBox

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Cartesian position expressed as x, y, and z coordinates with respect to a spatial origin and spatial orientation
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CartesianPosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Cartesian volume given by the lengths to x, y, and z directions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CartesianVolume

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Classification enables the specification where an Identifiable Entity belongs in a given classification scheme (such as OmniClass, UniFormat, CoClass, Talo2000, etc.)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Classification
An equipment for moving objects. The crane remains stationary during the movement and usually there is a difference in altitude in the origin and target location of the object movement.
Crane

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Machinery and tools used in construction activities. Equipment do not have a capability to operate activities by itself automatically.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Equipment

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Minimum bounding box of a geographical area determined by its minimum geographical position and maximum geographical position
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeographicBoundingBox

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Geographic position expressed in longitude, latitude and altitude with respect to a geographic coordinate system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: GeographicPosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A set of indentifiable entities. Examples are a procurement package, a shipment, a workgroup, or the walls of a space.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Group

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Identifier allows the specification of a (global or local) identifier, based on the given identification system (GUID, URI, room number in a building, etc.)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Identifier

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Identifiable information content. Examples are a BIM model, a drawing, a specification, an image, a message, and an issue. Separate from physical information carriers.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: InformationContentEntity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Location refer to particular places
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Location

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Material batch refers to the collection of homogeneous physical substance that participates in the construction project as the input of a process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: MaterialBatch

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Orientation in two dimensions given by the orientation angle from true north
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OneAngleOrientation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The dimensions of a spatial region
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialExtent

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A position in a space
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialPosition

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A quality that concerns the spatial aspects of an entity
Orientation given by three angles: angle about x-axis (alpha), angle about y-axis(beta) and angle about z-axis (gamma)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ThreeAngleOrientation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: TimeInstant
TimeInterval
Orientation of a plane in two dimensions given by its angle about true north (the strike) and the angle of its slope (the dip)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TwoAngleOrientation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An equipment for transporting shipments. The vehice also moves from origin to the target of the transportation activity. Examples are trucks or forklifts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Vehicle

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A site of work. There can be multiple different kinds of workspaces needed by an activity: labor crew space, equipment space, hazard space, and so on.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Workspace
